text: Subconfluent cultures of RD cells were synchronized in G0/G1 phase by serum deprivation (He et al., 2010) . Approximately 5 Ã— 10 5 cells were plated in a 6-well plate and maintained in serumfree medium for 24 h. After EV-D68 virus infection, fresh 10% DMEM was added to release the cells from G0/G1.
